## Prerequisites: Verify NuGet Configuration

**⚠️ IMPORTANT: Before proceeding, verify that your `nuget.config` includes the required Azure DevOps feeds with proper authentication.**

### Required Package Sources

Journey Framework packages (Journey.Kafka, which includes Journey.Orchestration) are hosted on Azure DevOps feeds. Your `nuget.config` must include:

**Minimum Required Feed:**
- **DIGeneralFeed**: `https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/lsportsltd/DataIntegrityInfra/_packaging/DIGeneralFeed/nuget/v3/index.json`

**Recommended Full Configuration:**

Create or verify `nuget.config` in your solution root or test project directory:

```xml
<?xml version="1.0" encoding="utf-8"?>
<configuration>
  <packageSources>
    <add key="nuget.org" value="https://api.nuget.org/v3/index.json" protocolVersion="3" />
    <add key="DIGeneralFeed" value="https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/lsportsltd/DataIntegrityInfra/_packaging/DIGeneralFeed/nuget/v3/index.json" />
    <!-- Add other LSports feeds as needed -->
    <add key="AutomationFeed" value="https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/lsportsltd/_packaging/AutomationFeed/nuget/v3/index.json" />
    <add key="InfrastructureFeed" value="https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/lsportsltd/Infrastructure/_packaging/InfrastructureFeed/nuget/v3/index.json" />
    <add key="DataIntegrityInfraFeed" value="https://pkgs.dev.azure.com/lsportsltd/DataIntegrityInfra/_packaging/DataIntegrityInfraFeed/nuget/v3/index.json" />
  </packageSources>
</configuration>
```

### Authentication Setup

Azure DevOps feeds require authentication. Choose one of the following methods:

#### Option 1: Configure Feed Credentials with PAT (Recommended)

If you have a Personal Access Token (PAT):

```bash
# Update each feed with credentials
dotnet nuget update source DIGeneralFeed \
  --username az \
  --password YOUR_AZURE_DEVOPS_PAT \
  --store-password-in-clear-text

# Repeat for other feeds as needed
dotnet nuget update source AutomationFeed \
  --username az \
  --password YOUR_AZURE_DEVOPS_PAT \
  --store-password-in-clear-text
```

#### Option 2: Use Azure Artifacts Credential Provider

Install and configure the Azure Artifacts Credential Provider:

```bash
# Install the credential provider
wget -qO- https://aka.ms/install-artifacts-credprovider.sh | bash

# Or on Windows (PowerShell):
iex "& { $(irm https://aka.ms/install-artifacts-credprovider.ps1) }"

# Then restore with interactive login
dotnet restore --interactive
```

#### Option 3: Manual packageSourceCredentials in nuget.config

Add credentials directly to `nuget.config` (⚠️ **Not recommended for committed files**):

```xml
<configuration>
  <packageSources>
    <!-- package sources here -->
  </packageSources>
  
  <packageSourceCredentials>
    <DIGeneralFeed>
      <add key="Username" value="az" />
      <add key="ClearTextPassword" value="YOUR_AZURE_DEVOPS_PAT" />
    </DIGeneralFeed>
  </packageSourceCredentials>
</configuration>
```

### Verify Authentication

Test that you can access the feeds:

```bash
# Try to search for Journey Framework packages
dotnet package search Journey.Kafka --source DIGeneralFeed
```

If successful, you should see package results. If you get a **401 Unauthorized** error, your authentication is not configured correctly.

### Common Authentication Issues

**Issue: 401 Unauthorized**
- Solution: Verify your PAT has "Packaging (Read)" permissions
- Solution: Check that PAT hasn't expired
- Solution: Ensure you're using the correct feed URL

**Issue: Package source not found**
- Solution: Verify the feed URL is correct
- Solution: Check your network can access pkgs.dev.azure.com

**Issue: Credentials not persisting**
- Solution: Use `--store-password-in-clear-text` flag (or configure credential provider)

