## Step 2: Install NuGet Packages

Add the required NuGet packages to your test project:

```bash
dotnet add package Journey.Kafka
dotnet add package KafkaFlow
dotnet add package KafkaFlow.Serializer
dotnet add package Confluent.Kafka
dotnet add package Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration
dotnet add package Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.Json
dotnet add package Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.EnvironmentVariables
dotnet add package Steeltoe.Extensions.Configuration.PlaceholderCore
dotnet add package NUnit
dotnet add package NUnit3TestAdapter
```

**Why these packages?**
- `Journey.Kafka`: Core Journey Framework (includes Journey.Orchestration as dependency)
- `KafkaFlow`: Kafka client abstraction
- `Confluent.Kafka`: Low-level Kafka operations (admin client for cleanup)
- `Microsoft.Extensions.Configuration.*`: Configuration management
- `Steeltoe.Extensions.Configuration.PlaceholderCore`: Environment variable placeholders

**Note:** Journey.Orchestration is the new name for what was previously called journey. It's automatically included when you install Journey.Kafka.

