## Best Practices

### 1. Use Unique Consumer Groups

```csharp
// ✅ Good - Unique per test project
public const string CONSUMER_GROUP = "your-service.integration-tests";

// ❌ Bad - Generic name might conflict
public const string CONSUMER_GROUP = "test-group";
```

### 2. Always Clean Up Consumer Groups

```csharp
[OneTimeSetUp]
public async Task OneTimeSetUp()
{
    await Setupjourney();
    await CleanupConsumerGroups();  // Clean before tests
}

[OneTimeTearDown]
public async Task OneTimeTearDown()
{
    await CleanupConsumerGroups();  // Clean after tests
}
```

### 3. Use Test Categories for Prioritization

```csharp
[Test, Category("P0")]  // Critical path - must always pass
public async Task Should_Process_Critical_Flow() { }

[Test, Category("P1")]  // Important features
public async Task Should_Handle_Edge_Case() { }

[Test, Category("P2")]  // Nice to have
public async Task Should_Support_Optional_Feature() { }
```

Run specific categories:
```bash
dotnet test --filter "Category=P0"
```

### 4. Set Appropriate Timeouts

```csharp
// Base timeout on your service SLA
TimeOut = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(30)  // For fast services
TimeOut = TimeSpan.FromSeconds(60)  // For slower processing
TimeOut = TimeSpan.FromMinutes(2)   // For batch operations
```

### 5. Use Descriptive Test Names

```csharp
// ✅ Good - Clear what is being tested
[Test]
public async Task Should_Process_Valid_Order_Successfully() { }

[Test]
public async Task Should_Reject_Order_With_Invalid_Customer_Id() { }

// ❌ Bad - Unclear test purpose
[Test]
public async Task Test1() { }

[Test]
public async Task OrderTest() { }
```

### 6. Add Helpful Console Output

```csharp
Console.WriteLine($"Processing message {inputMessage.Id}");
Console.WriteLine($"✅ Successfully processed in {elapsed}ms");
Console.WriteLine($"❌ Test failed: {ex.Message}");
```

### 7. Use Extension Methods for Message Extraction

Create reusable helpers in `Extensions/EnumerableExtensions.cs`:

```csharp
using Journey.Core.Messaging.Models;

namespace YourService.IntegrationTests.Extensions;

public static class EnumerableExtensions
{
    public static List<T> ExtractMessages<T>(this IEnumerable<ResponseContainer>? results) 
        where T : class
    {
        if (results == null)
            return new List<T>();
        
        return results
            .SelectMany(r => r.Messages)
            .Where(mc => mc.Value is T)
            .Select(mc => (T)mc.Value)
            .ToList();
    }
}
```

Usage:
```csharp
var outputMessages = messages.ExtractMessages<YourOutputDto>();
Assert.IsNotEmpty(outputMessages, "Should receive output messages");
```

### 8. Async/Await Best Practices

```csharp
// ✅ Good - Properly awaited
var messages = await waitForMessagesTask.Task;

// ❌ Bad - Blocking async code
var messages = waitForMessagesTask.Task.Result;  // Can cause deadlocks!
```

